<!-- ===============================================
     SECTION 2: WHY THIS AREA
================================================ -->
<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2efe9); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#c4912a; margin-bottom:1rem;">Local Expertise</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:300; line-height:1.2; color:#1c1917; margin-bottom:1.75rem;">A bayside suburb with genuine village character, the Esplanade lifestyle and strong family appeal.</h2>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Wynnum sits approximately sixteen kilometres east of the Brisbane CBD on Moreton Bay, with a foreshore character that sets it apart from most Brisbane suburbs at its price point. The Wynnum Esplanade and its adjoining wading pool, parklands and marina give the suburb a genuine coastal identity within metropolitan Brisbane. This is not waterfront in the prestige sense, but it is real bayside living: saltwater air, morning walks along the seawall, and a growing cafe and dining precinct centred on Wynnum Central that has transformed the suburb's daytime character over the past decade.
    </p>
