        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Wynnum property values are driven by bayside lifestyle access, Esplanade proximity, block size and the suburb's growing village dining and cafe precinct. Homes within walking distance of the Esplanade attract a premium, while the established owner-occupier streets north of the foreshore offer consistent family appeal. The suburb's relative affordability compared to similarly positioned coastal suburbs elsewhere in southeast Queensland is a key buyer draw.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#1c1917; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          How long does it take to sell a home in Wynnum?
          <span style="color:#c4912a; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Well-priced Wynnum homes typically sell within 28 to 45 days. The suburb draws families attracted by bayside living and space, and downsizers moving away from inner suburbs who want a village atmosphere and waterfront access. Lifestyle properties close to the Esplanade tend to attract wider buyer interest and sell more quickly when presented and priced well.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#1c1917; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What is the lifestyle like in Wynnum?
          <span style="color:#c4912a; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Wynnum offers a relaxed bayside lifestyle approximately 16 kilometres east of the Brisbane CBD. The Wynnum Esplanade, wading pool and foreshore parklands are central to the suburb's identity, and the growing Wynnum Central cafe and dining precinct has transformed the suburb's character. The train line connecting Wynnum to the CBD takes approximately 25 to 30 minutes, making it practical for city commuters.</p>
      </details>

