          Is Wynnum a good suburb to buy in right now?
          <span style="color:#c4912a; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Wynnum offers a rare combination of bayside lifestyle, established village character and relative affordability. The suburb's growing dining and retail precinct, reliable train access and strong community identity have increased its appeal with buyers who previously overlooked the eastern corridor. Block sizes are competitive relative to the price point and the suburb is attracting upgraders from across southeast Brisbane.</p>
